    "valve_count": 3,
    "notes": "Horn in F is a transposing instrument — written C sounds F (P5 lower). Uses 3 rotary valves operated by the LEFT hand (unique among brass). Double horns add a thumb trigger for the Bb side; this chart covers F side only. The overtone series is denser than trumpet, making partial selection more critical. Same valve combinations as trumpet but different note assignments due to the F fundamental."
